.TH MALLOC 3
.SH NAME
malloc, free \- memory allocation functions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include <stdlib.h>

void *malloc(unsigned nbytes);
void free(void *ap);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B malloc()
function allocates
.I size
bytes of memory and returns a pointer to the allocated memory.

The
.B free()
function releases memory previously allocated by
.B malloc().
If
.I ptr
is NULL, no action is taken.
The
.B malloc()
function returns a pointer to the allocated memory on success.
If allocation fails, NULL is returned.
.SH ERRORS
.B malloc()
may fail and return NULL if insufficient memory is available.
